<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Arch on Saitech</title><link>https://saitech.blog/tags/arch/</link><description>Recent content in Arch on Saitech</description><generator>Hugo -- gohugo.io</generator><language>en-us</language><lastBuildDate>Fri, 18 Jul 2025 00:00:00 +0000</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://saitech.blog/tags/arch/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Malware Found in AUR</title><link>https://saitech.blog/p/malware-found-in-aur/</link><pubDate>Fri, 18 Jul 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://saitech.blog/p/malware-found-in-aur/</guid><description>&lt;img src="https://saitech.blog/p/malware-found-in-aur/1.png" alt="Featured image of post Malware Found in AUR" /&gt;&lt;h2 id="the-issue"&gt;The Issue
&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Malware-laced packages were recently uploaded to the AUR by user 🔗&lt;b&gt;&lt;a class="link" href="https://aur.archlinux.org/packages?O=0&amp;amp;SeB=m&amp;amp;K=Quobblego&amp;amp;outdated=&amp;amp;SB=p&amp;amp;SO=d&amp;amp;PP=50&amp;amp;submit=Go" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
&gt;Quobblego&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="https://saitech.blog/p/malware-found-in-aur/2.png"
width="2500"
height="426"
srcset="https://saitech.blog/p/malware-found-in-aur/2_hu_1fd3a0e15b564e9.png 480w, https://saitech.blog/p/malware-found-in-aur/2_hu_4c96a2ce3d97672b.png 1024w"
loading="lazy"
class="gallery-image"
data-flex-grow="586"
data-flex-basis="1408px"
&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;These packages have been &lt;strong&gt;removed&lt;/strong&gt;, and the Arch team is aware, but to be safe, &lt;strong&gt;check your system to ensure you don&amp;rsquo;t have any of these installed&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id="affected-packages"&gt;Affected packages:
&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;librewolf-fix-bin&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;firefox-patch-bin&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;zen-browser-patched-bin&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3 id="newly-identified-malicious-packages"&gt;Newly identified malicious packages:
&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;ttf-ms-fonts-all&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;minecraft-cracked&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;ttf-all-ms-fonts&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;vesktop-bin-patched&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Source:&lt;/strong&gt;
🔗&lt;b&gt;&lt;a class="link" href="https://lists.archlinux.org/archives/list/aur-general@lists.archlinux.org/thread/7EZTJXLIAQLARQNTMEW2HBWZYE626IFJ/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
&gt;article&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="why-this-matters"&gt;Why this matters
&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;The AUR (Arch User Repository) is &lt;strong&gt;community-driven&lt;/strong&gt;. Anyone can upload packages, which means &lt;strong&gt;due diligence is your responsibility&lt;/strong&gt; before installing from the AUR.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Always &lt;strong&gt;review PKGBUILDs&lt;/strong&gt;, use trusted maintainers, and avoid blindly installing packages, especially &lt;code&gt;-bin&lt;/code&gt; builds from unknown uploaders.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="honorable-mention-clamav"&gt;Honorable mention: ClamAV
&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;🔗&lt;b&gt;&lt;a class="link" href="https://wiki.archlinux.org/title/ClamAV" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
&gt;ClamAV&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/b&gt; ican detect some malware &lt;strong&gt;on-demand&lt;/strong&gt;, but it will &lt;strong&gt;not protect you in real-time&lt;/strong&gt;. Use it to scan files occasionally, but remember that &lt;strong&gt;your brain and good hygiene are your best security layers on Linux&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
